    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age: 40 to 65 years old

          -  patients with medial osteoarthritis of knee of level 1 or 2 from ahlback's
             classification with High Tibial Osteotomy indication

          -  one sided indication

          -  well understanding of information note by patient, non-opposition to perform the
             research

          -  Affiliation to a national health insurance program

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  age &lt; 40 or &gt; 65 years old

          -  medial osteoarthritis of knee of level superior to 2

